{"title_page": "Taperoo railway station", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                = Taperoo\n| image               = TaperooRailwayStationAdelaide.jpg\n| caption             = \n| address             = Railway Terrace\n| borough             = [[Taperoo]]\n| coordinates         = \n| owned               = \n| operator            = \n| line                = [[Outer Harbor railway line|Outer Harbor Line]]\n| distance            = 18.2&nbsp;km from [[Adelaide railway station|Adelaide]]\n| platforms           = 2\n| tracks              = \n| structure           = \n| parking             = No\n| bicycle             = No\n| disabled            = \n| bus_routes          = None\n| code                = \n| zone                = \n| website             = \n| opened              = 1920\n| closed              = \n| rebuilt             = 1955\n| services            = \n{{s-rail|title=Adelaide Metro}}\n{{s-line|system=Adelaide|line=Outer Harbor|previous=Draper|next=Midlunga}}\n}}\n\n'''Taperoo railway station''' is located on the [[Outer Harbor railway line|Outer Harbor line]].<ref>[https://www.adelaidemetro.com.au/var/metro/storage/original/application/684c3f76dfe11ad139bbae9fa45d8cc5.pdf Outer Harbor & Grange timetable] Adelaide Metro 23 February 2014</ref> Situated in the north-western [[Adelaide]] suburb of [[Taperoo]], it is 18.2 kilometres from [[Adelaide railway station|Adelaide station]].\n\n== History ==\n{{Expand section|date=September 2017}}\nThis station was built in 1920. It was originally named Silicate Siding, and was renamed Taperoo on 22 November 1920.\n\nOriginally a step down [[Railway platform|platform]], it was replaced with the current [[island platform]] in 1955.\n\nThe station was upgraded in 2017 with a new shelter along with new signage and lighting.\n\n==Services by platform==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float: none; margin: 0.5em; \"\n|-\n!Platform\n!Lin